<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Runyon</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-10-28"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Telegram received this morning. I have seen minister for foreign affairs
                            and made urgent representations according to instructions. Immediate
                            action or reply not probable on account of present Government
                            conditions.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>